codes.0: Item is in the original language(s) of the work
codes.1: Item is a translation of the original work or an intermediate work
codes.2: Item contains translations other than translated summaries
codes.8: Expression data are coded in a separate linked authority record

a.label: has Language of text, soundtrack etc. in Language of the resource
a.description: The language of the text, soundtrack etc.

b.label: has Language of intermediate text when item is not translated from original in Language of the resource
b.description: The language of any intermediate translation.

c.label: has Language of original work in Language of the resource
c.description: The language of the original work when the item being recorded is a translation.

d.label: has Language of summary in Language of the resource
d.description: The language of any summaries or abstracts of the item or of works, articles, etc. contained within it.

e.label: has Language of contents page in Language of the resource
e.description: The language of the table of contents when this differs from the language of the text.

f.label: has Language of preferred source of information for the title page in Language of the resource
f.description: The language of the preferred source of information for the title pagewhen it differs from the language or languages of the text.

g.label: has Language of title proper if not first language of text, soundtrack, etc in Language of the resource
g.description: The language of the title proper when it differs from that in the first or only occurrence of the language of the text, soundtrack etc.

h.label: has Language of libretto, etc. in Language of the resource
h.description: The language or languages of the text when the item being catalogued includes the vocal/textual content of the work(s) printed as text, whether as accompanying material or printed with the item.

i.label: has Language of accompanying material (other than summaries, abstracts or librettos) in Language of the resource
i.description: The language or languages of accompanying material, such as programme notes, prefaces, commentaries, instructions etc.

j.label: has Language of subtitles in Language of the resource
j.description: The language(s) of subtitles (overprinted titles) of moving pictures when different from the language of the soundtrack.

c.description: The main grid or referencing system.

d.description: A subsidiary grid or referencing system which extends across the face of the cartographic material.

e.label: has Secondary grid and referencing system in Coded data field: cartographic resources: geodetic, grid and vertical measurement
e.description: A subsidiary grid or referencing system which appears in the form of marginal ticks.

g.description: The unit of measurement of heighting.

h.label: has Contour interval in Coded data field: cartographic resources: geodetic, grid and vertical measurement
h.description: The value of interval of the main contours (i.e. those contours which always appear when applicable) in the unit of measurement of heighting.

i.label: has Supplementary contour interval in Coded data field: cartographic resources: geodetic, grid and vertical measurement
i.description: The value of the interval of supplementary contours, i.e. contours used between main contours to increase the topographic expression of the area (e.g. in areas of low relief) or contours whose value is not repeated on the surface of the map.

l.description: The oceanographic equivalent of Unit of Measurement of Heighting, Contour Interval and Supplementary Contour Interval.
